React JS Framework from FB



Install
  1, Get brackets IDE installed
     a, sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/brackets
     b, sudo apt-get update
     c, sudo apt-get install brackets
  2, Get NPM installed
     a, sudo apt-get install -y nodejs
  3, Install React
     a, sudo npm install -g create-react-app
     b, sudo ln -s /usr/bin/nodejs /usr/bin/node


Create new app
  1, On debian-based system, make sure /usr/bin/node points to nodejs
  2, create-react-app helloworld
  3, cd helloworld && npm start
  4, You can now see the project in a browser window




Reference
  1, https://reactjs.org/docs/
  2, https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/A_re-introduction_to_JavaScript
